The food was ok, steak was not cooked to order and it took 20-30 minutes to come. But what got me was when the server brought my bill he had already added a 18% tip. For a party of 3. So I asked him when it became customary to automatically add gratuity for 3 people? He told me that was their policy sense the pandemic and I could talk to the manager. The manager proceeded to tell me the same thing. I told them they would not be taking my money and giving himself what he thought he deserved. I'm in the pandemic also. Besides that a tip is for the costumer to show their appreciation for the service and is not mandatory !!! With that said I left the tip as it was but I had to let them know it's not ok to take liberties with somebody's money!!!

The manager I spoke with did comp us drinks and dessert , and while we appreciated that kind gesture, it still will not change how disappointed we were especially for this to be a upscale place. Beware of shady bookkeeping! We received our receipt and the tax was at a 12% rate (supposed to be 10%) and the included 20% gratuity was calculated off of the TAXED portion of the bill (supposed to be off the untaxed portion).  Who knows how long this practice has gone on for. If the restaurant has profited off this practice for weeks, months, years, they are making an extra 3-5% per table.  Also we were at the table figuring out the difference at our bill for about 20 minutes after dinner, and the manager did not offer any considerations for the inconvenience.  For the supposed fine dining experience here, it came up much too short.

Where do I start!?! The ambience was beautiful when we arrived. Lights were low, there was a blue luminate light that traced the ceilings ever so nicely....it was very romantic!  A waiter came to take our drink menu, then our actual waiter Nelson came to review the menu with us since we had never been here before.  He was so patient and informative of the entire menu, from where the seafood comes from to what pairs nicely together. After we decided, we chose a ceasar salad, swordfish, fruits of the Sea, key lime pie and a coffee. The service was phenomenal!  Maybe five minutes after ordering, the salad was out and then less than ten minutes after, the entrees arrived. And the food was Excellently delicious!  The Fruit of the Sea entree included one jumbo prawn about half the size of your hand that tasted like lobster, two scallops (grilled perfectly) and resting comfortably in a butter sauce, and one crab cake (which was EVERYTHING!!! ALL Crab - No filler!) oh, and three asparagus. But the seafood was the star of that plate!  My husband had the swordfish, which he enjoyed. He said it was grilled perfectly!  It is a more firm fish, which is not my preference, however, he loved it! As a side he ordered the lobster Mac and cheese.  That was AMAZING! It was Rich yet not too heavy. I enjoyed the fact that there was broken pieces of lobster throughout the dish as oppose to one lump or very scarce pieces of lobster. For desert, key lime pie.... Oh my!......... This jumbo slice of pie (very much so a shareable size) was ever so refreshing and definitely had fresh lime and more than likely lime zest as well. It had such a refreshing zing that was a perfect finish for cleansing the palate after such an exquisite meal. We are from out of town, however, when we come back to town, this is definitely a must stop.  The Oceanaire Seafood Room, you have been #BeeStampApproved 🐝

Now, those that chose the steaks got steaks that were of decent quality, though routinely one temperature overcooked.  Maybe not surprising for a seafood restaurant.  The pasta was fine, if unremarkable.  The fish however, which about 10 of chose ranged from acceptable to had to be sent back.  Of the 10 of us 3 of us got fish that had grill marks, but once pulled apart was positively RAW inside. Not mildly undercooked, but so vastly undercooked as to be inedible.  How can a seafood place get the task that home cooks do successfully every single day, so wrong.  Grilling Mahi Mahi is not hard.  We certainly won't be back.
